<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.223227>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Gieysztoria guangdongensis Wang & Xia n. sp. (A) Photographed in life. (B) Sclerotic stylet in whole-mounted specimen (1, 2, 3 represent different depth of microscope view). (C) Dissection of sclerotic stylet. (D) Permanent slide stained by H. E. method. (E) Detail of reproductive system stained by H. E. method. (F) Ventral view of the male copulatory organ stained by H. E. method." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/223227/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.223228>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Gieysztoria guangdongensis Wang & Xia n. sp. Reconstruction of the sclerotic stylet." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/223228/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

